'''Álvaro Fidalgo Fernández''' (born 9 April 1997) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Real Betis]]. Born in Spain, he represents the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

==Club career==
===Real Madrid===
Born in Hevia, [[Siero]], [[Asturias]], Fidalgo joined [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s [[La Fábrica (Real Madrid)|La Fábrica]] in 2012, from [[Sporting de Gijón]].<ref name="Marca">{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/real-madrid/2019/07/14/5d2a322146163fc5228b459f.html|title=Fidalgo, el chaval que recordaba a Iniesta y que ahora quiere convencer a Zidane|trans-title=Fidalgo, the youngster who reminded of Iniesta and who now wants to convince Zidane|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=14 July 2019|accessdate=6 September 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elcomercio.es/asturias/siero-centro/alvaro-fidalgo-centrocampista-20170720162230-nt.html|title=Álvaro Fidalgo, un centrocampista de ley|trans-title=Álvaro Fidalgo, a draft central midfielder|publisher=[[El Comercio (Spain)|El Comercio]]|language=es|date=20 July 2017|accessdate=6 September 2020}}</ref> On 21 June 2016, after finishing his formation, he was loaned to [[Segunda División B]] side [[CF Rayo Majadahonda]] for [[2017–18 Segunda División B|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rayomajadahonda.es/noticia/acuerdo-con-el-real-madrid-por-alvaro-fidalgo|title=Acuerdo con el Real Madrid por Álvaro Fidalgo|trans-title=Agreement with Real Madrid for Álvaro Fidalgo|publisher=CF Rayo Majadahonda|language=es|date=21 June 2016|accessdate=6 September 2020}}</ref>

Fidalgo made his senior debut on 20 August 2016, starting in a 0–0 draw against [[Sestao River Club]]. In July 2017, after being a regular starter, he returned to his parent club and was assigned to [[Real Madrid Castilla|the reserves]] also in the third division.

Fidalgo made his first team debut for Real Madrid on 6 December 2018, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Vinícius Júnior]] in a 6–1 home routing of [[UD Melilla]], for [[2018–19 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2018/12/06/5c095d6fe2704e016c8b45f7.html|title=Fran Garcia and Alvaro Fidalgo handed senior debuts by Solari|publisher=Marca|date=6 December 2018|accessdate=6 September 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elcomercio.es/deportes/futbol/real-madrid-jugador-sierense-alvaro-fidalgo-20181206212527-nt.html|title=El sierense Álvaro Fidalgo debuta con el Real Madrid|trans-title=''Sierense'' Álvaro Fidalgo debuts with Real Madrid|publisher=El Comercio|language=es|date=6 December 2018|accessdate=6 September 2020}}</ref> For the [[2019–20 Segunda División B|2019–20 season]], he was named [[Captain (association football)|team captain]] of [[Raúl (footballer)|Raúl]]'s Castilla.

===Castellón===
On 25 August 2020, Fidalgo signed a three-year deal with [[Segunda División]] newcomers [[CD Castellón]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdcastellon.com/fichaje-alvaro-fidalgo-nuevo-jugador-del-cd-castellon/|title=FICHAJE: Álvaro Fidalgo, nuevo jugador del CD Castellón|trans-title=SIGNING: Álvaro Fidalgo, new player of CD Castellón|publisher=CD Castellón|language=es|date=25 August 2020|accessdate=6 September 2020}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 12 September, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Jorge Fernández Lucas|Jorge Fernández]] in a 2–1 away win against [[SD Ponferradina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/ponferradina-vs-castellon/cronica/2020/09/12/5f5ceab9e2704eb81a8b45a0.html|title=La victoria del debutante Castellón llega en la última jugada y de rebote|trans-title=Th victory of the debutant Castellón arrives in the last play and from a rebound|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=12 September 2020|accessdate=12 September 2020}}</ref>

===Club América===
On 1 February 2021, despite featuring regularly at [[CD Castellón|Castellón]], Fidalgo joined Mexican club [[Club América|América]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdcastellon.com/comunicado-oficial-i-alvaro-fidalgo/|title=Comunicado oficial {{!}} Álvaro Fidalgo|trans-title=Official announcement {{!}} Álvaro Fidalgo|publisher=CD Castellón|language=es|date=1 February 2021|accessdate=4 February 2021}}</ref> On 2 June 2021, Club América confirmed the permanent signing of Fidalgo. During his time with the club, he helped the team secure three league championships.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Álvaro Fidalgo sale del América tras cinco años en el club: Fuentes|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mexico/nota/_/id/16254191/america-alvaro-fidalgo-salida-liga-mx-futuro-equipo-europa|website=ESPNdeportes.com|date=2026-01-31|access-date=2026-02-01|language=es}}</ref>

=== Betis ===
On 1 February 2026, Fidalgo returned to Spain to join [[Real Betis]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=El Real Betis Balompié y América de México acuerdan el traspaso de Álvaro Fidalgo|url=https://www.realbetisbalompie.es/noticias/actualidad/el-real-betis-balompie-y-america-de-mexico-acuerdan-el-traspaso-de-alvaro-fidalgo-32132|website=realbetisbalompie|access-date=2026-02-01|language=es-ES}}</ref>

==International career==
In February 2026, FIFA approved Fidalgo’s request to switch his international allegiance to [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]], having previously represented [[Spain national football team|Spain]] at youth level.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-02-06 |title=FIFA: Álvaro Fidalgo ya es elegible por México |url=https://www.espn.com.mx/futbol/selecciones/nota/_/id/16276546/alvaro-fidalgo-seleccion-mexicana-elegible-fifa-cambio-federacion |access-date=2026-03-29 |website=ESPN.com.mx |language=es}}</ref> The following month, he received his first call-up and made his senior debut on 28 March in a friendly against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2026-03-19 |title=Fidalgo celebra llamado de México con su debut en Europa League |url=https://www.espn.com.mx/futbol/champions-league/nota/_/id/16461071/alvaro-fidalgo-europa-league-debut-betis-seleccion-mexicana |access-date=2026-03-29 |website=ESPN.com.mx |language=es}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Fidalgo's grandfather [[Rafael Fidalgo Ciprés|Rafael]] was also a footballer. A [[Defender (association football)|defender]], he played professionally for [[UP Langreo]], [[Real Oviedo]] and [[Caudal Deportivo]].<ref name="Marca"/> He gained Mexican citizenship after spending more than 5 years in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://americamonumental.bolavip.com/noticias/alvaro-fidalgo-dejo-abierta-la-posibilidad-de-jugar-con-mexico-en-el-futuro-soy-mexicano|title=Álvaro Fidalgo dijo lo que nadie esperaba sobre representar al Tri en el futuro: "Soy mexicano"|date=1 February 2026|website=Águilas Monumental}}</ref>

